New Records: Jason Holder took 5 wickets and scored 27 runs, including a hat-trick in the last four deliveries.
Sam Billings scored 41 runs, the highest score for England in the innings.
Key Match Events: England collapsed to 10 wickets for 162 runs, their lowest score in a completed T20I.
West Indies scored 179/4, with key partnerships from Kieron Pollard (41) and Rovman Powell (35).
Pre-Game Insights: West Indies elected to bat first after winning the toss.
This was the 5th T20I match of the series, with the series result being 3-2 in favor of West Indies.
Post-Match Reflections: Jason Holder was named Player of the Match and Player of the Series.
West Indies' victory marked a significant moment in their series triumph.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was a day-night game held at Kensington Oval, Barbados.
